In a group of 191 consecutive patients who underwent operation at the Mayo 
Clinic for isolated pulmonary valve stenosis between 1956 and 1967, late results 
were excellent. In patients surviving operation before the age of 21 years, 
long-term survival was similar to that in an age- and sex-matched control 
