Projections of future populations are fraught with uncertainties based on past 
fertility and immigration trends, and assumptions about medical science and 
lifestyles. The U.S. Census Bureau and the Social Security Administration may be 
unduly cautious in their assumption that the mortality decline of the past two 
decades cannot continue; it may be sustained for the next half century. 
